# {{project.name}} - Backend Setup Guide

## Quick Start

### Prerequisites

- Node.js >= 18.0.0
- Bun >= 1.0.0 (recommended) or npm
- PostgreSQL 13+ (required for BetterAuth authentication)

### Installation

```bash
# Install dependencies
bun install

# or with npm
npm install
```

### Database Setup

#### 1. Create PostgreSQL Databases

```bash
# Create main application database
createdb {{snakeCase project.name}}

# Create BetterAuth authentication database
createdb {{snakeCase project.name}}_auth
```

#### 2. Configure Environment

Copy `.env.example` to `.env` and update the database credentials:

```bash
cp .env.example .env
```

Update the following values in `.env`:
- `DATABASE_PASSWORD`: Your PostgreSQL password
- `DB_HOST`: PostgreSQL host (default: localhost)
- `DB_PORT`: PostgreSQL port (default: 5432)
- `DB_USER`: PostgreSQL user (default: postgres)

#### 3. Run Migrations

```bash
# Run all migrations
bun run migrate

# or with npm
npm run migrate
```

#### 4. Seed Database (Optional)

```bash
# Seed initial data
bun run seed

# or with npm
npm run seed
```

### Start Development Server

```bash
# Start with hot-reload
bun run start:dev

# or with npm
npm run start:dev
```

The API will be available at `http://localhost:{{config.port}}`

## Features

### Authentication (BetterAuth)

- **Email/Password Authentication**: Sign up and sign in with email/password
- **Session Management**: Secure sessions with 1-day expiration
- **Rate Limiting**:
  - 5 sign-up attempts per minute
  - 10 sign-in attempts per minute
  - 10 requests per minute for other endpoints

#### Auth Endpoints

```bash
# Sign up
POST /api/auth/sign-up
{
  "email": "user@example.com",
  "password": "SecurePassword123",
  "name": "User Name"
}

# Sign in
POST /api/auth/sign-in
{
  "email": "user@example.com",
  "password": "SecurePassword123"
}

# Get current session
GET /api/auth/session

# Sign out
POST /api/auth/sign-out
```

### Business Rules Engine

The application includes a business rules engine powered by `json-rules-engine`:

- **Validation**: Enforce data quality rules
- **Prevention**: Block invalid operations
- **Notification**: Trigger business events

#### Rules Endpoints

```bash
# Evaluate rules
POST /api/rules/evaluate
{
  "entityType": "{{#each entities}}{{#if @first}}{{tableName}}{{/if}}{{/each}}",
  "data": { /* entity data */ },
  "action": "create" | "update" | "delete"
}

# Validate against rules
POST /api/rules/validate
{
  "entityType": "{{#each entities}}{{#if @first}}{{tableName}}{{/if}}{{/each}}",
  "data": { /* entity data */ },
  "action": "create"
}

# List entities with rules
GET /api/rules/entities
```

